The paper presents two novel algorithms for learning formulas in Linear Temporal Logic (LTL) from examples, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithms also involve propositional Boolean logic (cs.PL) and decision trees (cs.SE), which are relevant subfields of computer science. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance and scalability of the algorithms, which could be of interest to researchers in logic (cs.LO).
